{"000-section": {"000-title": "Assam Fee Waiver Scheme 2019 \u2013 Parental Income Limit Hiked for Students"}, "001-section": {"000-title": "Assam Fee Waiver Scheme 2019 parental income limit hiked, students with annual family income less than Rs. 2 lakh can get free admission in UG / PG courses in all provincialized & govt. colleges & 5 universities"}, "002-section": {"000-title": "Assam Fee Waiver Scheme 2019", "001-normal": "The salient features and highlights of the Fee Waiver Scheme Assam are as follows:-", "002-listElement": "- If the parents of students are working either in state or central govt. jobs, then their monthly salary slip needs to be produced while taking admission in colleges.", "003-listElement": "- In case parents are working in private organization, then salary slip from employer is necessary indicating their salary is less than Rs. 2 lakh p.a.", "004-listElement": "- If parents are not working either in govt or private institution or organization, then certificate from the circle officer or mouzader would be considered.", "005-listElement": "- In addition to the above 3 conditions, if principal and admission committee in their wisdom feels that the annual family income of student is less than Rs 2 lakh, then concerned principal can provide free admission to those students.", "006-listElement": "- Fee Waiver Scheme Assam also covers all the Persons with Disability (PWDs) without any consideration of parental income."}}